rComments: Brian Axel is a rather interesting individual and sort of weird.He is, however, extremely funny and a great professor. He is a great choice for ethics since he's so unorthodox. The class was extremely easy and although his lectures were entertaining you don't really need to go to them to pass the class, I would suggest it for sheer pleasure though.
Brian is a wonderful professor! He engages his students. He elaborates very clearly and uses examples from life that students can relate to. Brian is very intelligent and friendly. I loved Phil 22.
